%% CloudFront OAC — S3 Origin Access Pattern
%% Blueprint refs: Task 3.1 (edge security), Task 5.2 (data protection)
%%
%% OAC keeps S3 private. Only CloudFront can access it.
%% OAI is deprecated — OAC is always the exam answer.

flowchart LR
    subgraph USERS["Internet"]
        USER["👤 User"]
        ATTACKER["🔴 Attacker"]
    end

    subgraph EDGE["CloudFront Edge"]
        CF["CloudFront Distribution<br/>+ WAF rules<br/>+ Geo-restrictions<br/>+ Access logging<br/>──────────<br/>OAC configured"]
    end

    subgraph AWS["AWS (private)"]
        S3["📦 S3 Bucket<br/>──────────<br/>Block Public Access: ON<br/>Bucket policy: ONLY<br/>CloudFront service principal<br/>+ SourceArn condition"]
        KMS["🔑 KMS Key<br/>──────────<br/>Key policy allows<br/>CloudFront kms:Decrypt<br/>(for SSE-KMS objects)"]
    end

    USER -->|"HTTPS"| CF
    CF -->|"SigV4 signed<br/>request (OAC)"| S3
    S3 -.->|"Decrypt"| KMS

    ATTACKER -->|"Direct to S3"| S3
    S3 -->|"❌ DENIED<br/>not CloudFront"| ATTACKER

    style CF fill:#ff9900,color:#fff
    style S3 fill:#3366cc,color:#fff
    style KMS fill:#dd4444,color:#fff
    style ATTACKER fill:#ff4444,color:#fff
